## Success Criteria
- [ ] All 7 source modules exist (error, config, parser, transpiler, container, validator, preprocessor)
- [ ] src/lib.rs declares all modules with \`pub mod\`
- [ ] src/lib.rs re-exports key types (Result, ValidatorError, ValidatorPreprocessor)
- [ ] \`cargo build\` succeeds without errors
- [ ] \`cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings\` passes
- [ ] No \`#![allow(clippy::pedantic)]\` at crate level

## Anti-Patterns (FORBIDDEN)
- NO \`#![allow(clippy::pedantic)]\` at crate level (defeats purpose)
- NO stub implementations using \`todo!()\` or \`unimplemented!()\`
- NO placeholder TODOs without clear comments
- NO empty modules (each must have at least one type or function)
- NO missing module declarations in lib.rs

Dependencies (2):
  [parent-child] mdbook-validator-wkm (open): Epic: Project Scaffolding with Strict Linting and First-Class Testing [P0]
  [blocks] mdbook-validator-i0t (closed): Task 4: Create .config/nextest.toml with test profiles [P0]

## Key Considerations (SRE Review)

**Edge Case: Clippy pedantic warnings**
- Skeleton code may trigger clippy::pedantic warnings
- Common issues: missing docs, unused fields, must_use
- Allowed exceptions in Cargo.toml: missing_errors_doc, missing_panics_doc, module_name_repetitions, must_use_candidate
- If new warnings appear, add targeted #[allow] on specific items, NOT crate-level

**Edge Case: Unused imports**
- Some imports may appear unused until implementation
- Use #[allow(unused_imports)] on specific imports if needed
- Do NOT use crate-level #\![allow(dead_code)]

**Reference: CLAUDE.md file organization**
- Must match exactly: error.rs, config.rs, parser.rs, transpiler.rs, validator.rs, container.rs, preprocessor.rs
- lib.rs must re-export key types for external use
